<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>EYES,EARS,NOSE,MOUTH</title>
    <link href="style.css" rel="stylesheet" />
    <script defer src="main.js"></script>
  </head>

  <section class="hero">
    <header class="head">
      <marquee> of New York City</marquee>
    </header>
    <div>
      <h1 class="MainTitle">
        <span>EYES,<br />EARS,<br />NOSE,<br />MOUTH</span>
      </h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="float-layer">
    <img class="floaty" src="/eye.png" alt="eyes" />
    <img class="floaty" src="/eye2.png" alt="eyes2" />
    <img class="floaty" src="/nose.png" alt="nose" />
    <img class="floaty" src="/mouth.png" alt="mouth" />
    <img class="floaty" src="/ears.png" alt="ears" />
  </div>

  <section class="desForm">
    <div class="copy">
      <h3>
        <p>
          <br />
          <br />This is a space to capture a moment when you felt something deeply—so much that you
          wanted to document it.
        </p>

        <p>
          It can be anything: a picture, a description of something you heard, smelled, or tasted,
          and maybe the general location or name of the neighborhood.
        </p>

        <p>
          Fill in your moment here, and it will become part of a collective journal—a map of how we,
          as a community, feel.
        </p>

        <p>
          We will be using a color code to represent what you felt:
          <span class="chip chip-sight">a sight</span>,
          <span class="chip chip-scent">a scent</span>,
          <span class="chip chip-taste">a taste</span>,
          <span class="chip chip-sound">a sound</span>, or
          <span class="chip chip-unnamed">a feeling you cant quite name</span>. (Designers
          privilege: I assigned the colors.)
        </p>

        <p>
          You can pick a borough, or add a location if. Lets see what our shared emotional landscape
          looks like.
        </p>
      </h3>
    </div>

    <div class="submitInfo">
      <h3>
        <br />
        <br />
        <form action="/submit" method="GET">
          <label>
            Name / Pseudonym
            <input type="text" name="guest" placeholder="optional" />
          </label>
          <br /><br />

          <label>
            Describe your moment
            <br />
            <textarea
              name="message"
              rows="5"
              cols="50"
              placeholder="what happened / what did you feel?"
            ></textarea>
          </label>
          <br /><br />

          <label>
            Type of sensation
            <select name="sense" required>
              <option value="" disabled selected>choose one</option>
              <option value="sight">Sight</option>
              <option value="scent">Scent</option>
              <option value="taste">Taste</option>
              <option value="sound">Sound</option>
              <option value="unnamed">Other</option>
            </select>
          </label>
          <br /><br />

          <label>
            Borough
            <select name="borough" required>
              <option value="" disabled selected>choose one</option>
              <option value="Manhattan">Manhattan</option>
              <option value="Brooklyn">Brooklyn</option>
              <option value="Queens">Queens</option>
              <option value="Bronx">Bronx</option>
              <option value="Staten Island">Staten Island</option>
              <option value="Other">Outside NYC / Other</option>
            </select>
          </label>
          <br /><br />

          <label>
            Location (optional)
            <input type="text" name="location" placeholder="neighborhood / landmark" />
          </label>
          <br /><br />

          <input type="submit" value="Add to journal" />
        </form>

        <br />
        <br />
        <a href="/collection"><p>View All</p></a>
      </h3>
    </div>
  </section>
</html>
